- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as coding theory is often used in cryptography.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses constructions and bounds on codes.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as coding theory has applications in network coding.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but cannot be completely ruled out as the paper may discuss the computational complexity of constructing or decoding codes.
